Definition.WordDefinition: Reestablish \Re`["e]s*tab"lish\ (r?`?s*t?b"l?sh), v. t. To establish anew; to fix or confirm again; to restore; as, to re["e]stablish a covenant; to re["e]stablish health. [1913 Webster]

reestablish v : bring back into original existence, use, function, or position; "restore law and order"; "reestablish peace in the region"; "restore the emperor to the throne" [syn: {restore}, {reinstate}]
